# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# quite_change/ — local gitignore
# This file SUPPLEMENTS the parent repo's .gitignore. See note at
# the bottom about the parent's `data/` rule which we override here.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Senior's test runs from the interactive web UI ────────────────
# Auto-saved by research/serve.py to research/staging/{code}.json.
# These are unvalidated exploratory runs — never auto-merged into
# the canonical sector files. Promote keepers explicitly with:
#   python -m research.promote_staging --promote <code> --to-sector <SECTOR>
research/staging/*.json

# ── IT entries promoted from staging but not yet folded into the IT module ──
# Written by promote_staging.py when --to-sector IT is used. These
# are pending integration into build/build_view.py and shouldn't be
# committed until reviewed and merged into the IT data structure.
data/it_staged_additions/

# ── Partial / interrupted IT extension sweep (69 files, unvalidated) ──
# Uncomment to also exclude from commits if you don't want
# work-in-progress data tracked. Leave as-is to commit them.
# verification_batches/it_extension/

# ── Python local caches (reinforces parent .gitignore) ────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/

# ── Local notes / scratch files ──
*.bak
*.tmp
*.swp
notes-local.md

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT — parent .gitignore conflict
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The parent repo's .gitignore contains `data/` to exclude a heavy
# Tempest data cache at the outer level. That pattern also matches
# THIS folder's data/ — which would block the canonical sector files
# (data/company_research_*.json) from being committed.
#
# Fix this ONE of two ways (parent .gitignore lives outside this
# folder, so this file alone cannot un-ignore data/):
#
#   Option A — edit parent .gitignore to scope the rule:
#     change `data/` → `/data/`     (only matches outer-repo root)
#     OR add a negation:  `!quite_change/data/`
#
#   Option B — git add -f when committing canonical sector files:
#     git add -f quite_change/data/company_research_*.json
#     git add -f quite_change/data/sector_config.json
#     git add -f quite_change/data/it_census_universe.csv
#
# Option A is the cleaner long-term fix.
